originalText.text: I signed up for this because I think Dr. Diaz is fantastic and I had a terrible experience with his receptionist, trying to reach him when I was having trouble breathing.  She never put me through.  I still think he is a great doctor and I appreciate being able to reach him easily, but this is a very expensive program and, fortunately, I am not sick enough to really take advantage of it.

originalText.text:
When searching for a new Dr., I believe the person who answers the phone sets the tone for what is to follow.
In my case, from the first call, I encountered the loveliest receptionist Maria who set the tone.
I walked into the beautiful office and the vibe was WOW, clean and friendly. The nurse who took my vitals...delightful!

In walked Dr. Diaz! Friendly, warm, good listener he asked the right relevant questions and had a great sense of humor to boot! I felt like he totally understood and diagnosed my problem!

The icing on the cake was getting an appointment with a new specialist at a convenient time, the same week I called!
When was the last time that happened for you?

I HIGHLY recommend Dr. Diaz.

Robbie Jo Michaels

originalText.text: Love Doctor Diaz as he is a great diagnostician. However, be prepared to wait. Never have I been in his office and been taken at the time of my appointment. At a minimum, you will wait at least an hour after your scheduled appointment time to be seen. Block off your work schedule if you plan to see him in the middle of the day.
